      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, much like my heart. It is so cold in this manor, and the silence... the silence is louder than any scream. He is gone, and with him, the very sun has vanished from my sky. I feel as though I am nothing more than a ghost already, wandering through halls that no longer recognize me. There is no light left to seek, only the long, velvet embrace of the dark.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
